text.tspan: Thanks. This works great! One last question. I have added two buttons to the he
der.primary that trigger a search and a share panel to slide open below the main
bar. It works perfectly except when I open and then close the hav slider. After I
click off the nav to close it the click event on the search button fires automatically
opening the search panel. If I open and close the nav menu again the search panel
closes. It happens whether I use jQuery or straight up JavaScript. I think its happe
ning because when I click off the nav menu it treats the rest of the page as a
“button” thus triggering the click event on the search button. Any clue how I might
prevent this from happening? I’m think if only the nav button was hot when trying
to close the nav menu it might solve the problem, but perhaps not the best for usa
bility.
Thanks again for any light you can shed. E
